To define dynamic viscosity the density of the solution under study was measured by the bottle method. Since solution density depends on its temperature, the density and kinematic viscosity measurement were performed at the same temperature. Dynamic viscosity was calculated in accordance with formula (3). t t t ρ ⋅ ν = η

(3) t η - liquid dynamic viscosity at the corresponding temperature, Pascal sec; tρ – liquid density at the corresponding temperature, kg/m3;

The accuracy of dynamic viscosity determination calculated according to this procedure does not exceed 1 %. There were four basic stages of the investigations conducted: 1. The first stage determined the dependence of viscosity and density of nickel catholyte solution on its temperature and nickel and chlorine ions concentration. Catholyte from the nickel tank house of Polar Branch of OAO “MMC “Norilsk Nickel” served as feed catholyte. It is used for the electrolysis cells and has the following composition: Ni 2+ - 71.9 g/dm3; Cl - - 39.5 g/dm3; SO4 2- - 120.0 g/dm3; Na +
